        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "BRA-6406: revert preflightCompaction hard-throw to graceful-skip (HR-5 regression fix on lossless-claw 0.11.2 no-op)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix HR-5 regression introduced in `openclaw` v2026.5.22 where `preflightCompaction` throws a hard `Error` when `lossless-claw` 0.11.2 returns its legitimate `{ ok: true, compacted: false, reason: \"already under target\" }` no-op response. The throw propagates to the Telegram bot dispatch loop, where it is caught as `dispatchError` and emits the canned HR-5 fallback string `\"Something went wrong while processing your request. Please try again.\"` to the user — a regression vs the v2026.5.19-beta.1 behavior which gracefully skipped the no-op.\n\nThe lossless-claw 0.11.2 side is clean (BRA-5666 fix intact). The bug is entirely on the openclaw runtime side of the integration.\n\n## Root cause (file:line precise)\n\n### Pre-upgrade (v2026.5.19-beta.1) — graceful skip ✓\n`dist/agent-runner.runtime-COnAR88A.js:637-640`\n```js\nif (!result?.ok || !result.compacted) {\n    logVerbose(`preflightCompaction skipped: sessionKey=${params.sessionKey} reason=${result?.reason ?? \"not_compacted\"}`);\n    return entry ?? params.sessionEntry;\n}\n```\n\n### Post-upgrade (v2026.5.22) — hard throw ✗\n`dist/agent-runner.runtime-C3rgesYz.js:647-650`\n```js\nif (!result?.ok || !result.compacted) {\n    const reason = result?.reason ?? \"not_compacted\";\n    logVerbose(`preflightCompaction failed: sessionKey=${params.sessionKey} reason=${reason}`);\n    throw new Error(`Preflight compaction required but failed: ${reason}`);\n}\n```\n\n### Lossless-claw contract\nOn compact() lossless-claw 0.11.2 returns one of seven reason strings. **`already under target`** is the correct no-op case — there's nothing to compact when the session is already under the compaction target. The pre-upgrade runtime treated this as graceful skip; the post-upgrade runtime treats it as a fatal precondition violation.\n\n### Canned-text emission site\n`dist/bot-D0mzNk0g.js:7099`\n```js\nconst fallbackText = dispatchError ? \"Something went wrong while processing your request. Please try again.\" : EMPTY_RESPONSE_FALLBACK;\n```\n\n## Reproduction (verbatim live exchange)\n\n- 2026-05-26T17:54:46Z — operator sent to chat 162648370: `BRA-6400 done — WhatsApp re-linked, cron re-enabled. Close it.`\n- 2026-05-26T17:55:00.292Z — Janus outbox sent to chat 162648370: `Something went wrong while processing your request. Please try again.` (Telegram messageId 24900).\n\n### Gateway log correlation\n```\n2026-05-26T10:54:59.275-07:00 [diagnostic] message dispatch completed: channel=telegram sessionKey=agent:main:telegram:direct:162648370 source=replyResolver outcome=error duration=8810ms error=\"Error: Preflight compaction required but failed: already under target\"\n2026-05-26T10:54:59.276-07:00 [diagnostic] message processed: messageId=24899 outcome=error duration=9390ms error=\"Error: Preflight compaction required...\"\n```\n\n## Live runtime sha256s\n\n| File | sha256 | Mtime | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `dist/agent-runner.runtime-COnAR88A.js` (v2026.5.19-beta.1, pre-upgrade backup) | `9fcd63f0c5e2d39202cb63b44a2dd5d0d6475ce90a9bf981f26a6ee403097762` | 2026-05-25 13:42 | Working — graceful skip |\n| `dist/agent-runner.runtime-C3rgesYz.js` (v2026.5.22, currently deployed) | `010583db2068d9384e9baed40a67bdc4317b6fc0e007577e91b20c8243243ebb` | 2026-05-26 14:49 | Buggy — hard throw |\n\nSource-file sha256s after the merge commit `a61e2b5`:\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.ts`: `ee6ab84891884229eb0aa9fd0fcc1f2fca93eb5defcb95b1e6136aed3fc85945`\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts`: `874676ed57c1ddf7a37700111a4618e85283a87db5a8745bee7a49cf630f3a22`\n\n## Local merge\n\n- Source patch commit: `cbbe87bb375f546ed4440db1a00b3321eb653f8f` (`fix(memory): skip no-op preflight compactions`)\n- Local merge commit: `a61e2b56660a38c9c57a87a837c7c7cbac45e531` (`--no-ff` merge of source onto v2026.5.22 release tip)\n- Branch: `aaronahmadi:robo/master/audit-fix-batch`\n- Verification at merge head:\n  - `git diff --check`: exit 0\n  - `vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts`: 1 file passed, 25 tests passed\n  - `oxfmt --check`: all matched files use correct format\n  - `tsgo -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental`: exit 0\n\n## Production telemetry\n\nThe patched runtime has been running live on the operator's Mac Studio (sole openclaw v2026.5.22 host) for >24h continuous with zero regression evidence: no `Preflight compaction required but failed` errors in the gateway error log, no further HR-5 canned-text emissions to operator chat, and no observed change in compaction-path latency or memory footprint.\n\n## Divergence note for reviewers\n\nThis PR targets `main` (operator's brief said `master`; upstream renamed master → main, GitHub PR creation rejected `--base master` with \"Base ref must be a branch\"). The PR HEAD branch is on a v2026.5.22 release lineage that is 1531 commits ahead of upstream `main` and 81 commits behind. The substantive fix is just two commits (`cbbe87bb` + `a61e2b5`); the rest is the v2026.5.22 release history. If the equivalent guard is already in place on `main` (a quick check shows `agent-runner-memory.ts` exists on `main` with different content), please cherry-pick `cbbe87bb` rather than merging this PR directly. Filed via fork because operator does not have write to `openclaw/openclaw`.\n\n## Reference\n\n- Operator-side ticket: BRA-6406 (regression report, gateway log links)\n- Carry-forward ticket: BRA-6549 (push blocker resolved by this PR)\n- Source-patch attribution: Co-Authored-By: Paperclip <noreply@paperclip.ing>\n",
